{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566620","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566620"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:45:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:45:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18856"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18856","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18856"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.01,0.96,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11589"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107877"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11589","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11589"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18856"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90293"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11309"},{"type":"tags","id":"11310"},{"type":"tags","id":"11312"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27281"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27282"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37355"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107877","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107877"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor is preparing to make a specialist referral for a patient. The doctor wants to ensure the referral contains all essential information for optimal patient care.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following combinations contains the most essential components of a specialist referral?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Medication list and family history","Investigation results and social history","Reason for referral and current management","Vital signs and systems review","Imaging reports and previous specialist letters"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAs per current Medicare (Services Australia) requirements, when referring a patient to a specialist or consultant physician for treatment, the referral must include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERelevant clinical information about the patient\u2019s condition for which they are being referred\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESignature of the referring health professional\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA date of referral.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOf the options above therefore the most essential combination includes\u00a0\u003Cstrong\u003Ereason for referral and current management\u003C/strong\u003E. These two elements provide the core clinical information about the patients condition for which they are being referred which allows for initial specialist assessment and triage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe remaining options, such as\u00a0\u003Cstrong\u003Efamily history, investigation reports, social history, systems review and previous specialist letters\u003C/strong\u003E\u00a0while all containing important supporting information for some referrals, are not necessarily essential for all referrals and should be included on an as needed basis.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Effective specialist referrals should include key clinical information, the health professionals signature and a referral date.","The most complete referral information enables appropriate triaging and optimal specialist consultation.","Clear communication in referrals improves patient safety and care coordination between healthcare providers."],"references":["Medical Board 